<statement>
<p>Note <m>\displaystyle\frac{{{V}_{{1}}{P}_{{1}}}}{{{T}_{{1}}+{273}}}=\frac{{{V}_{{2}}{P}_{{2}}}}{{{T}_{{2}}+{273}}}</m> with temperature in Celsius.</p>
<p>If <m>\displaystyle{V}_{{1}}={V}_{{2}}={0.250}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{P}_{{1}}={2214}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{T}_{{1}}={16.0}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{T}_{{2}}={32.0}</m>, what is <m>\displaystyle{P}_{{2}}</m>? <fillin characters="6" /></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>2,340</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{{V}_{{1}}{P}_{{1}}}}{{{T}_{{1}}+{273}}}=\frac{{{V}_{{2}}{P}_{{2}}}}{{{T}_{{2}}+{273}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{{0.250}\cdot{2214}}}{{{16.0}+{273}}}=\frac{{{0.250}\cdot{P}_{{2}}}}{{{32.0}+{273}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{{0.250}\cdot{2214}}}{{{16.0}+{273}}}\cdot\frac{{{32.0}+{273}}}{{{0.250}}}={P}_{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2336.5743944637}={P}_{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2340}\approx{P}_{{2}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

